Sentencas: Micro-tubular solid-oxide fuel cell consisting of a 10-mu m thick (ZrO2)(0.89)(Sc2O3)(0.1)(CeO2)(0.01) (ScSZ) electrolyte on a support NiO/(ScSZ) anode (1.8 mm diameter, 200 mu m wall thickness) with a Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 (GDC) buffer-layer and a La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF)/GDC functional cathode has been developed for intermediate temperature operation.
Titulo: Development of micro-tubular SOFCs with an improved performance via nano-Ag impregnation for intermediate temperature operation

Sentencas: The functional cathode was in situ formed by impregnating the well-dispersed nano-Ag particles into the porous LSCF/GDC layer using a citrate method.
Titulo: Development of micro-tubular SOFCs with an improved performance via nano-Ag impregnation for intermediate temperature operation

Sentencas: The cells yielded maximum power densities of 1.06 W cm(-2) (1.43 A cm-2, 0.74 V), 0.98 W cm(-2) (1.78 A cm(-2), 0.55V) and 0.49 W cm(-2) (1.44 A cm(-2), 0.34 V), at 650, 600 and 550 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Development of micro-tubular SOFCs with an improved performance via nano-Ag impregnation for intermediate temperature operation
